      <div1 type="letter">
        
        <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.21-22_0001" />

        <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>

        <opener>
                                                                                        <dateline>25 Nov. 1916 &#8212;</dateline>

          <salute>Dear Mr Neihardt, &#8212;</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>I am leaving for Minneapolis on the first of December, and expect to pass through Bancroft on Monday the 4th December. If you are going to be at home I want to stop over a train and pay my respects 
          
          <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.21-22_0002b"/>
          
          to the author of <title>Hugh Glass.</title> I expect to reach Omaha the night before <add>at 9.55</add> and stay at the likeliest hotel, whatever it is. Can you send me a line there letting me know you will? There seems to be a train from Omaha at 8.25 <hi rend="caps">A.M.</hi> which would set me down at Bancroft at 10.50; and I could go on at 4.42 <hi rend="caps">P.M.</hi> to Sioux City, and so to Minneapolis. I am the 
                                                                                                            
          <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
          
          <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.21-22_0002a"/>

          more encouraged to suggest this, as I have just talked with Sterling, who tells me by all means to do it.</p>
        <closer>
                                            <salute>Faithfully yours</salute>
          
                                              <signed>J G Howard</signed>
        </closer>

                        <note type="Neihardt">John Galen Howard</note>

      </div1>
    </body>
    
